        <h2 id="scones">Scones</h2>
        <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/food/croissant.png" alt="scone or croissants" width="200">
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 45mins</li>
            <li>Serves: 24 </li>
        </ul>
        
        <table class="scones">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>flour</td>
                <td>400gm<td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>veg oil</td>
                <td>200ml<td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>yeast</td>
                <td>5gm</td>
            </tr>
           </tbody>
        </table>   
           
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Sieve the flour to remove air.<br>
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Mix floour with yeast and stir till mix is uniform<br>
        <strong>Step 3:</strong> Add Veg oil to the mix and mix with a stand mixer till dough is think and consistent<br>
        <strong>Step 4:</strong> pinch small pieces that will be baked into scones
</p>
        
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://laurenslatest.com/simple-scone-recipe/">Some recipes websites</a></em></p>
    
    <h2 id="sponge_cake">Sponge cake</h2>
    <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/food/cake.png" alt="sponge cake" width="200">
    <ul>
        <li>Time: 55mins</li>
        <li>Serves: 24</li>
    </ul>
    <table class="sponge_cake">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Ingredients</strong></td>
                <td><strong>Quantity</strong></td>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Flour</td>
                <td>350gm</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Magerine</td>
                <td>350gm</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Eggs</td>
                <td>7</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
    <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Sieve the flour to remove air.<br>
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Mix Magerine,sugar and Eggs and beat till mix is fluffy<br>
        <strong>Step 3:</strong> Add flour to the mix and mix with a mixer till its all mixed consistently<br>
        <strong>Step 4:</strong> pour the mix into the already greased baking pan and bake at 320 degrees
</p>
<p><em>Source: <a href="https://natashaskitchen.com/easy-sponge-cake-genoise/">Some recipes websites</a></em></p>

<h2 id="fruit_salad">Mixed Fruit Salad</h2>
    <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/food/fruits.png" alt="mixed fruit salad" width="200">
    <ul>
        <li>Time: 15mins</li>
        <li>Serves: 12</li>
    </ul>
    <table class="fruit-salad">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Ingredients</strong></td>
                <td><strong>Quantity</strong></td>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Black berries</td>
                <td>200gm</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>star berries</td>
                <td>10</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Pineapples</td>
                <td>1</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Tangerines</td>
                <td>3</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
    <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Cut all fruits to small shaped pieces.<br>
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Mix all fruits into one bowl<br>
        <strong>Step 3:</strong> Add yoghurt or honey as preferred<br>
        <strong>Step 4:</strong> serve in 12 bowls of equal portions
</p>
<p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/214947/perfect-summer-fruit-salad/">Some recipes websites</a></em></p>
